adr_address: 270 7th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Sightglass Coffee

reviews.text: I'm in love with their vanilla cold brew. The coffee here is good and the pastries are delicious!! Really cool and urban atmosphere

Coffee was good and the building is a really interesting space, large and with a second floor that also looks like there is a separate area for private events. Came during a very hot day, no air conditioning there and that could have made the baristas grumpy, cause they were not friendly and not willing to explain there drinks to someone that had never been there before.
Coffee is good. Space is better. People watching is the best. And if you're lucky, you'll get to pet someone's adorable dog outside.

I never want to leave this place, the atmosphere is so lovely. The coffee and scone are amazing. The nice young man that took my order was pleasant and he called me friend. This was my most favorite part of this SF trip. I'm not only leaving my heart in San Francisco, I'd like to leave right here. Here you go Sightglass, it's all yours ❤.
great in house roasted beans . strong and lingering after taste. second floor sitting is a bit warm tho even in winter. maybe laptops are emitting so much heat here

adr_address: 1231 Market St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
formatted_address: 1231 Market St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Starbucks

reviews.text: Staff was great! I got my usual of an iced coffee and it tasted a bit lighter than usual. This location has nowhere for you to sit... it only serves as a grab and go. Just FYI.

Good small starbucks.
No seating options.
Very few tables.
Good for takeaway.
Ordered chai latte... Cannot taste any chai flavor. Never had this happen at any of the other locations.
Starbucks fails at everything, as usual. Bad staff and everything tastes bad.
Nice and friendly people and the evening people always know my name. Quick and efficient service. There are 3 Starbucks near me but I always come here. I just wish the store was remodeled.

adr_address: 1122 Folsom St, San Francisco, CA 94103-3928, USA
formatted_address: 1122 Folsom St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: BrainWash

reviews.text: I'm just sad, sad, sad! Brainwash is permanently closed!! This was the best laundromat in San Francisco. Friendly staff, great food, awesome entertainment, and a clean, clean laundry facility. I wish the best of luck to all the people who made Brainwash a fun place to do your laundry!!
So sad they closed. Really good food that wasn't The New SF price. RIP little SF wonder.
Do laundry and eat brunch. Free voucher available at Hospitality House 🏠 on Sixth Street. Great staff. Excellent facilities.

Clean, well organized and pleasant, unlike most laundromats in the city. First time I went, my wife and I set all our machines up to wash, played some pinball and ordered a burger ("The Burger of Doom"). Just as we finished eating the surprisingly tasty burger, an open mic comedy night was featured on the little stage of the cafe! Pretty rad little place!
Excellent laundromat... It has a caffe and even live entertainment. It close a little early... but is well looked after.

adr_address: 289 8th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Wicked Grounds

reviews.text:
Updated January 9, 2018.
I just received the email 2 days ago. Wicked Grounds is going out of business after tomorrow closing.

They will be missed by many and for varied reasons.   

Original Post:
For those of us working the night shift, having a place to enjoy a fresh pressed coffee or espresso along with a fresh pastry on the way to work and at nine o'clock at night is a treasure.
The menu features soups, salads and sandwiches made fresh and with quality ingredients (the creamed cheese slathered upon the toasted bagel is the creamed- chessiest).
Staff is friendly and engaging. They will bellow out your order when ready, out of necessity. 
Good crowd too. Not the typical customer base from a suburban Starbucks. 
Nice place to hang out at...and you can take that comment literally,  if you choose to.

Awesome kinky cafe. Nice Leather and rope for sale. The staff was very sweet and friendly. The Turkey melt was bomb and the salad was delicious!! I would come here all the time if I lived in San Francisco. Definitely a place to check out.

The table was not clean, I started cleaning it myself with some paper napkins, a server walked right next to me and didn't offer help.
They serve coffee in disposable cups even when you say you are going to drink it there. Cream on the coffee was frozen cold.
The attendant who took our order didn't have the best attitude. There were literally just four people at the store and the servers didn't bother to bring items to the table, they would just call the orders out loud for us to pick them up, when we're were only 10ft away from them. Bagels took forever.
They used the same knife to cut my goat cheese bagel and my wife's cream cheese bagel, therefore, my wife's bagel tasted like goat cheese (which she hates). We were so displeased with the whole experience that we didn't even bother to tell them about the goat cheese. We just took off. 
It is expensive, not that clean, service is terrible.. I can't understand how everybody is giving 5 stars.
Amazing! I've been told about this place for years from a friend. I'm so happy that I got to go here when I visited San Francisco. Awesome coffee, amazing food, and the coolest people!

Interesting places it's basically a fetish shop with coffee and food sounds kinda gross when you put it that way but it's super clean and the staff is really nice. The bathrooms could use a good scrub down not gonna lie. Good coffee and I heard their food is really good I didn't personally get to try it. Definitely worth the visit if you're not squeamish about sexuality.

adr_address: 1390 Market Street, 107, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
formatted_address: 1390 Market Street, 107, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
name: Starbucks

reviews.text: The coffee is what you'd expect from Starbucks. The place isn't a good place to stay - it's tiny, and all the power outlets are simply not working. They used to have wireless charging and they are removed too.
The same as every other over priced coffee shop in SF. It's ok
I think it’s small but nice
Post finding my phone; charging it downloading the app in the new phone, and getting discount,  in Lui, notary. I couldn't use the bathroom first.smhh.ok.
Great staff and prompt service. One of the best Starbucks I have been to. Only 4 stars as their wireless charging table is not functioning and only 1 outlets for customers to use.

adr_address: 272 McAllister St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
formatted_address: 272 McAllister St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
name: Soluna Cafe & Lounge

reviews.text: Food was fair but over priced. Atmosphere practically non-existent. I was greatly underwhelmed.
This was a great place for dinner before the ballet.  Short walk to either the Opera House or Symphony Hall.  Good food, service and a full bar if you just want cocktails.

Food here is alright. Nothing special and it is quite expensive actually. I paid 15$ for a small serving size of Mac n cheese which tasted like plain Mac n cheese just with fancy cheese that didn’t even taste that good. The menu choice here also does not have a lot of variety. There was about 4 choices for actual meals to eat. Also a worker here (I’m pretty sure he was the manager ) was very rude to these old ladies that had walked in when it was closing time.
Nice atmosphere. The wait staff seemed a bit thin/overworked but friendly. The steak was great. The nicoise salad was just okay as the seared tuna didn't seem fresh.
Katie & I loved the Civic Burger for a quick lunch ...and being close to Civic Center

adr_address: 1246 Folsom St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
formatted_address: 1246 Folsom St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Vega Coffee

reviews.text: Best spot to grab a cup in this part of town...small location but the coffee is thee best...cento for life!!

This place is great. Always fast even if there's a small line. But even if there is, the owner is always talkative. And the coffee is great. I usually get a macchiato which has good balance but it can sometimes taste like the espresso is a little under or over extracted. Overall I love this place. 

It is cash only!! So be careful of that one.
Vega is great! Raoul and co. are always friendly and helpful. Try their home-made oat bars.

Best cappuccino in the city - never burnt, always perfect! I've had it here at least 20 times (worked nearby) and it's so much better than Sightglass' and Blue Bottle's. The staff is friendly, especially the slightly round guy whose name I forget. The owner refused to take shortcuts, which is amazing. Also good croissants (get them before they run out, before 8:30 usually).
Raoul was great! We appreciated the friendly  conversation and sending off with coffee beans to try at home. Vega Cafe is a wonderful find in SOMA.

adr_address: 1298 Howard St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
formatted_address: 1298 Howard St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Starbucks

reviews.text: The Batista was so friendly! She helped my friend, who didn't even know what espresso was, pick out the perfect drink for her! She loved it! Good times!

I don't like Starburnt. They over roast their beans and the flavor is too strong and harsh for me. Really overpriced for a cup of bad  coffee. 

The company is predatory in putting local cafes out of business by offering landlords higher rent than currently paid. Support local cafes with individual personality, not cookie cutter cafe "stores".
Very good service,especially the barista Mary Lou,she has a very upbeat and genuine personality.
Go to peets unless you like paying 4 dollars for a cup of hot water i thought this was a coffee shop
This is my favor ☕ place I love it

adr_address: 142 McAllister St, San Francisco, CA 94102-4907, USA
formatted_address: 142 McAllister St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
name: Celtic Coffee Company

reviews.text: Just moved into this neighborhood last week, my wife had already known about it so she took me. Had the best tuna melt I'd had, like, ever. So good I cried during the end credits. Came back today for the sequel, it was just as good but not necessarily better. That being said, I hope the story never ends. Lovely place.
Cool spot with murals and lots of seating.  Take advantage  of on line ordering to have food ready when you arrive.

A bit pricey and staff tends to have higher amounts of miscommunication between ordering something and then picking it up. Colleagues and I have all experienced this - receiving the wrong order, someone else grabbing an unintended order. The space is clean and open, but will only be purchasing a simple small coffee in the future.
Great for a quick bite. Also great space to work on your laptop
Very nice and spacious local cafe serving up well sized delicious sandwiches.  There is also a selection of alcoholic beverages and coffees.

adr_address: 1145 Market St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
formatted_address: 1145 Market St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Chez Nous Cafe

reviews.text: Best croissant I've ever had, and the rest of the food looked good too. Elegant little tables but small enough to be inconvenient if you ordered more than a pastry. Honest staff - I ducked back in to take a call away from noisy street, and the server thought the (modest) tip was money I had forgotten. Has WiFi.
I love it here! Feels liks Paris, the best coffee I had in the US so far and the almond crossaont is amazing! There aren't any electric sockets, so not ideal if you're looking for a place to work

C C replaces Caffè Trinity with not much changes done to interior. Layout remain the same just a few area of brightened up keeping that luxury cafe feel. The former business signage are still visible, but expect to change in the near future. Sandwiches and salads will start sometime late July. Coffee beans are from Verve (Santa Cruz CA) and pastries are deliver by a local artisan bakery. Hours are 7am-7pm M-F, holiday and weekend closed.

adr_address: 1301 Mission St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
formatted_address: 1301 Mission St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Coffee Cultures

reviews.text: I ordered a toasted bagel with cream cheese. The server added sea salt to make the flavor pop out. Found them personable and warm; a memorable experience.
Delicious Everything bagel with jalapeno cream cheese! Wish the service is a little bit faster.
Stumbled upon this place this morning, got one of the best cappuccinos I’ve ever had and an amazing ham and cheese chutney!

Almond croissant and any  beverages​ on menu is the way to go here. Best to come 8-8:30am to avoid lines. The staff are wonderful people and you'll be  acknowledged prior to walking in. They followed​ specific details on any custom made drinks. Nice lounge area in back not visible from the front. Got me almond croissant and vanilla almond latte as a almond lover, I get everything with almond in them. Most importantly is that it's not a chain coffeehouse and they're​ as local as it gets.
Amazing coffee, amazing staff and a lovely, romantic bar.

adr_address: 64 6th St, San Francisco, CA, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
formatted_address: 64 6th St, San Francisco, CA, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Pentacle Coffee

reviews.text: My favorite new place to get coffee. So much so I go out of my way to have meetings and friendly catch ups there. Bobby is delightful and it feels great supporting a new business by a dedicated longtime San Franciscan. His experience helping start Four Barrell should inform you that this is a delicious pour every time!

I work across the street from this soon to open business. It's really refreshing to see someone investing in this area. The transformation from a barber shop to a coffee shop has been incredible to watch. Bobby has a cult following when it comes to his barrista skills. I can't wait to support this small locally owned business! ♥️
Love this place!! Great aesthetic, great people, and awesome to have a legit art gallery in back. Will definitely be frequenting.

This cafe is a great place in a not-so-great neighbourhood. But this is also an upcoming neighbourhood and has other great places surrounding it. Reminds me a lot about four barrell in the super early days. The coffee is great and you should try the special cajeta latte. Places like this need our support, so drop by and have your meetings there :)

I'll admit, I'm a sucker for two things.  Excellent coffee, and authentic, superior service.  Pentacle Coffee rocks in every way.  I adore this place, and it's already my daily midday coffee break (I work at San Francisco AIDS Foundation, 2 blocks away).

vicinity: 64 6th St, San Francisco, CA, San Francisco

adr_address: 1309 Howard St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
formatted_address: 1309 Howard St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Chantal Guillon Patisserie

reviews.text: This is the only Chantal Guillon place that has cakes and pastries afaik, in addition to their great macaroons. They are also the only place I know in the city  for getting Mariage Freres teas. A patisserie I love to visit every time I’m in the area.
The macarons are very good, but also very pricey. This makes a wonderful gift, however. Also, the ice cream stuffed macarons are simply amazing. Get them with some coffee.
Made FRESH daily Macarons!!! Simply delightful and delicious!

The macarons are exquisite. They couldn't be fresher and melt in your mouth with an impressive amount of flavor. Chantal Guillon also offers a very nice selection of small foods, wines and teas. Worth the price.
Great chocolate croissants and macarons.

adr_address: 1019 Market St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
formatted_address: 1019 Market St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: David Rio Chai Bar

reviews.text: This is my favorite coffee shop in SF. David and the staff are incredibly friendly — great selection of snacks and chais. Even the music is good ambience — def check this place out!
Amazing chai. I can hardly wait to go back and try the other flavors.
Highly recommend their Tiger Spiced Chai or their Matcha Latte. Nice atmosphere and spacious. Also comfortable seats.
Meanie gives classes on Latte Art here. She is great. The Chair is great also

Had absoubtely the BEST chai Ive ever had in my life here and I intentionally always order Chai Spice Lattes and Ive had them from literally all over the US and this one wins in everyway hands down! If you love Chai then you have to make the trip out here ❤❤❤

adr_address: 1355 Market St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
formatted_address: 1355 Market St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: The Market

reviews.text: On the pricey side for groceries, but considering where it's located, that shouldn't come as a surprise. Generally clean and well stocked with basics. Just don't come here looking for more exotic ingredients. Nice to have all the food vendors in one spot, though some are better than others (hint: avoid tacos). Update: stumbled in on Taco Tuesday for $2 tacos from 2P.M. to 5P.M. No, the uninspiring tacos prepared on cold tortillas are still definitely not worth it.

This is a consistent go-to spot for a quick and reasonably priced dinner. The salad bar is a good staple while the hot bar rotates through a variety of healthy and less than healthy selections. There are also pizza, burrito, poke, and other options from vendors around the perimeter of the market.

Expensive.
The table in the cafe are sometimes not clean. Prepared food is high quality, and tea is good. Store is otherwise very clean and nice. 
Net net I prefer Whole-foods, because Whole-foods is less expensive.

pleasant grocery market with an artisanal vibe.  more enjoyable as a food court than grocery store: hot food/salad bar, sandwiches, pizza, Mexican, and poki bowl counters surround the grocery section.
he Marketplace has some decent food options and quick grocery stop. Prices are expensive but location is close to work.

adr_address: 981 Mission St, San Francisco, CA 94103-2912, USA
formatted_address: 981 Mission St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Covo

reviews.text:
Got the opportunity to visit Covo during the 
SF Undiscovered last Saturday. Covo is a great place to hold your next event, party or business meeting. The bar had excellent drinks and food.
Thank you for hosting SF Undiscovered!
Very nice place. We had a conference with around a 100 people there and I really enjoyed being there. Very generous and high room. Very good food!
Amazing co-working space, community, and staff. Perfect place to work for entrepreneurs and digital nomads alike.
Nice and clean place. Don't go there without tour reservation if you want to get space from them. They are helpful but don't want to show their space while you don't have appointment for tour.
The space here is amazing. Plenty of open space, room for collaboration and a cafe inside!

adr_address: 1098 Howard St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
formatted_address: 1098 Howard St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Tony Baloney's

reviews.text: Recommended by the hotel doorman at the Holiday Inn.  Damn the sandwiches are delicious.  We had a Rueben and an Italian. The R was amazing and the Italian was delicious. Loved the bread for the Italian. Highly recommended
Love this place. They're always super friendly and quick. It's a little pricey for the basics and the bottled beverages are overpriced, but hey, it's San Francisco.
Great for any time of day. Breakfast sandwiches are hot and delicious. All kinds of lunch options.
The best veggie bagel sandwich ive ever eaten!
Newyork italianz sandwich. My fav

adr_address: 1355 Market St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
formatted_address: 1355 Market St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Blue Bottle Coffee

reviews.text: Excellent Blue Bottle outpost! The coffee is as brilliant as in all of their locations. This one is a very small branch, geared for take out. The staff were exceptionally friendly. My iced latte was gorgeous. There is some outdoors seating in the courtyard, though probably not specific to Blue Bottle.
Good coffee, friendly staff. The best place to taking coffee and sandwich to go

Heard that this place was the one HAVE TO try so we went there last April on our way to Union Square. The place was pack!!!! Line up was loooonnnggg ... but it was worth the wait. Love the coffee. Good place for quick meeting (business) as i saw lots of people in "work" clothes maybe its morning tea too. But didnt try any food as I am more curious about the coffee.

Met a former colleague here for coffee mid-afternoon and it’s a pretty typical Blue Bottle, though a bit smaller than expected.  That said, I suppose they want people to enjoy the shared courtyard rather than linger in the store.  The barista was very friendly, too.
To-go place for high-end coffee in SOMA SF. You'll probably find a queue anytime you go, but the staff is good to talk to, coffee is surely good and has an understated look which is good.
